The $\alpha$-$T_3$ model interpolates between the pseudospin $S$=1/2 honeycomb lattice (HCL) of graphene, and the pseudospin $S$=1 dice (or $T_3$) lattice via the parameter $\alpha$.  Fig.~\ref{fig:intro}(a) depicts the $\alpha$-$T_3$ lattice, with three atoms per unit cell, where sites $A$ and $B$ make up the HCL with hopping amplitude $t$, and site $C$ sits at the center of the hexagon, connected only to site $B$ with hopping amplitude $\alpha t$. We will refer to $\alpha=0$ as graphene, and $\alpha=1$ as the dice lattice throughout this paper.  The low-energy tight-binding Hamiltonian for the $\alpha$-$T_3$ model~\cite{raoux:2014} is given by

