In this section, we derive the DC Hall conductivity of the $\alpha$-$T_3$ lattice from the grand potential via the magnetization.  To begin, we employ the Streda formula $e \frac{\partial M}{\partial\mu}=\sigma_H(\mu)$ to relate the Hall conductivity to the grand potential

